ressors"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"Woe to those who devise iniquity"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and plot evil on their beds!"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["At morning’s light they accomplish it"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["because the power is in their hands."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"They covet fields and seize them;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["they take away houses."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["They deprive a man of his home,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["a fellow man of his inheritance."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"Therefore this is what the LORD says:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“I am planning against this nation a disaster"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["from which you cannot free your necks."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Then you will not walk so proudly,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for it will be a time of calamity."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"In that day they will take up a proverb against you"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and taunt you with this bitter lamentation:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["‘We are utterly ruined!"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["He has changed the portion of my people."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["How He has removed it from me!"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["He has allotted our fields to traitors.’”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"Therefore, you will have no one in the assembly of the LORD"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["to divide the land by lot."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Reproof of False Prophets"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Ezekiel 13:1–16)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"“Do not preach,” they preach."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["“Do not preach these things;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["disgrace will not overtake us.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"Should it be said, O house of Jacob,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["“Is the Spirit of the LORD impatient?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Are these the things He does?”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Do not My words bring good"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["to him who walks uprightly?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"But of late My people have risen up"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["like an enemy:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["You strip off the splendid robe"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["from unsuspecting passersby"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["like men returning from battle."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"You drive the women of My people"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["from their pleasant homes."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["You take away My blessing"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["from their children forever."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"Arise and depart,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for this is not your place of rest,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["because its defilement brings destruction—"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["a grievous destruction!"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"If a man of wind were to come"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and say falsely,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“I will preach to you of wine and strong drink,”",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["2:11"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["“I will prophesy to you for wine and strong drink”"]}]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["he would be just the preacher for this people!"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Remnant of Israel"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Micah 5:7–15)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"I will surely gather all of you, O Jacob;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I will collect the remnant of Israel."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["I will bring them together like sheep in a pen,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["like a flock in the midst of its pasture—"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["a noisy throng."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"One who breaks open the way"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["will go up before them;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["they will break through the gate,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and go out by it."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Their King will pass through before them,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the LORD as their leader."]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"3"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Rulers and Prophets Condemned"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"Then I said:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Hear now, O leaders of Jacob,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["you rulers of the house of Israel."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Should you not know justice?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"You hate good and love evil."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["You tear the skin from my people"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and strip the flesh from their bones."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"You eat the flesh of my people"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["after stripping off their skin"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and breaking their bones."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["You chop them up like flesh for the cooking pot,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["like meat in a cauldron.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"Then they will cry out to the LORD,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["but He will not answer them."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["At that time He will hide His face from them"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["because of the evil they have done."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"This is what the LORD says:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“As for the prophets"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["who lead My people astray,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["who proclaim peace"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["while they chew with their teeth,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["but declare war against one"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["who puts nothing in their mouths:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"Therefore night will come over you without visions,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and darkness without divination."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["The sun will set on these prophets,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and the daylight will turn black over them."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"Then the seers will be ashamed"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and the diviners will be disgraced."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["They will all cover their mouths"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["because there is no answer from God.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"As for me, however, I am filled with power"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["by the Spirit of the LORD,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["with justice and courage,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["to declare to Jacob his transgression"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and to Israel his sin."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"Now hear this, O leaders of the house of Jacob"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and rulers of the house of Israel,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["who despise justice"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and pervert all that is right,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"who build Zion with bloodshed"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and Jerusalem with iniquity."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"Her leaders judge for a bribe,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["her priests teach for a price,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and her prophets practice divination for money."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Yet they lean upon the LORD, saying,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["“Is not the LORD among us?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["No disaster can come upon us.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"Therefore, because of you,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Zion will be plowed like a field,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Jerusalem will become a heap of rubble,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and the temple mount a wooded ridge."]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"4"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Mountain of the House of the LORD"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Isaiah 2:1–4)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"In the last days the mountain of the house of the LORD"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["will be established as the chief of the mountains;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["it will be raised above the hills,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and the peoples will stream to it."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"And many nations will come and say:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Come, let us go up to the mountain of the LORD,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["to the house of the God of Jacob."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["He will teach us His ways,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["so that we may walk in His paths.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["For the law will go forth from Zion"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and the word of the LORD from Jerusalem."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"Then He will judge between many peoples"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and arbitrate for strong nations far and wide."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Then they will beat their swords into plowshares"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and their spears into pruning hooks."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Nation will no longer take up the sword against nation,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["nor will they train anymore for war."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"And each man will sit under his own vine